---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com';
const description = 'Contact the editorial team at hospitalbillnegotiationcalc.com for corrections, feedback, or questions about our calculator and guides.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p>For corrections, feedback, or questions about the calculator or guides, email the editorial team at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>What We Can Help With</h2>
  <p>We read every message and respond to: factual corrections (if you have identified an error in the calculator methodology, a statute citation, or a guide — include the specific claim and the source you believe is more accurate); feedback on the calculator or guide content; and questions about the site's methodology or editorial standards.</p>
  <p>Corrections are reviewed within five business days. Verified factual corrections are reflected in the content and noted on the affected page.</p>

  <h2>What We Cannot Help With</h2>
  <p>We cannot provide legal advice, medical advice, or individualized billing consultation. We cannot advise on your specific hospital bill, evaluate a specific financial assistance denial, or tell you whether a specific charge on your bill is correct. These require professional judgment that goes beyond the scope of an informational resource.</p>
  <p>If you need individualized help with a hospital bill, the following resources may be useful: hospital patient advocate offices (most large hospitals have one and access is free); nonprofit patient advocacy organizations; and medical billing advocates (fee-based professionals who review bills and negotiate on patients' behalf — typically charging a flat fee or a percentage of savings achieved).</p>

  <h2>Response Time</h2>
  <p>We aim to respond to all messages within five business days. We cannot guarantee responses to every message and do not respond to requests for case-specific billing advice or legal analysis.</p>

  <p>Return to the <a href="/">calculator</a> or see the <a href="/about">about page</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
